# M4 — Credit Packs via MoonPay/Helio (atelier-v0.1-beta-2)

Implementation plan for the credit-acquisition path. Ships **data-credit and compute-credit one-off packs over the existing MoonPay/Helio provider lane**, persists an `expired` terminal state on `billing_checkouts` with a background sweeper, and lands a Leptos credits modal + sidebar chip that learn about new balances by re-fetching entitlements on window focus. Spending integration is M5.

**Scope axis**: Milestone-series (M-axis), not Engine-iteration. Not logged in the Atlas session log.

**Author profile**: solopreneur PhD-final-year senior Rust engineer; spec is for self-execution.

> **Revision history.**
> - *2026-06-01a* — first draft (assumed trait seam; later found inaccurate).
> - *2026-06-01b* — corrected against the real `atelier-overledger` seam for a **direct-Stripe** lane.
> - *2026-06-01c (this version)* — **dropped the direct-Stripe lane entirely.** Decision (grilling session): MoonPay/Helio already covers *both* rails — fiat cards (Stripe-as-middleman inside Helio's iframe) *and* native crypto — so a second, direct-Stripe integration earns nothing in beta-2 beyond a middleman fee saved, at the cost of a whole new trust boundary (own Stripe key, HMAC verification, second webhook route, second SKU representation). Keeping one provider is the right beta call. `crates/stripe` stays the skeleton it is today. This rewrite re-scopes M4 around the MoonPay lane that already works; net new logic is essentially **one sweeper + the credits UI**.

