## §2 Decisions ledger

Each row: axis → choice → one-line rationale. **Q1–Q8 are the 2026-06-01c grilling-session decisions** that define this version; they supersede the prior draft's Stripe-direct Q3/Q4/Q7/Q10–Q14.

| Q  | Decision | Rationale |
|----|----------|-----------|
| Q1 | **Single provider: MoonPay/Helio only.** Delete the direct-Stripe lane for beta-2; `crates/stripe` stays a stub. | MoonPay already does fiat cards (Stripe-as-middleman) *and* crypto. A second integration adds a trust boundary (own key, HMAC, second webhook, second SKU space) and saves only a middleman fee — not worth it in beta. |
| Q2 | **Two separate single-kind credit packs:** `DataCredits` + `ComputeCredits`. No bundles. | Fits the model verbatim: one `Sku` → one `CreditKind` → one `CreditsPurchased` event → one ledger row, exactly as `webhook_paylink.rs` already maps. Un-gating `ComputeCredits` is `is_v1` + a test fix (`price_usd` is already 100). |
| Q3 | **Correlation via the `checkout_id` round-trip** (`additionalJSON`); the **trust anchor is our `billing_checkouts` row**, never the wire amounts. Webhook with no `checkout_id` → `400`. | Async, stateless confirmation must attribute to the right user/SKU; reading kind from the row's `Sku` (not Helio's reported `quantity`) prevents over-crediting. Already how the lane works. |
| Q4 | **Two idempotency layers**, orthogonal: `(provider_id, event_id)` PK (*same event again*) + checkout-status "Race D" guard incl. in-tx re-check (*same checkout again / concurrent*). `200` on no-op. | A = retried/duplicated identical event; B = a second event hitting an already-settled checkout, plus the concurrency window. Already in tree; M4 keeps it. |
| Q5 | **Persist `expired` only.** Add `succeeded_at` + `expired_at` columns; a 30 s sweeper flips `pending` → `expired` once `now() > expires_at`. **No `failed` state** (nothing on the MoonPay lane writes it). | 3 reachable states (`pending → {succeeded, expired}`), all with real writers. A `failed` state would be unreachable spec debt — and your house rule forbids a state with no transition that can fire it. |
| Q6 | **Poll-on-focus for live balance — no SSE.** Webapp refetches `GET /api/payments/entitlements` on window-focus. | The beta UX is "leave to a Helio tab and come *back*"; the return *is* a focus event, so a focus-refetch updates the balance exactly when the user is looking — with zero backend push machinery (no `PaymentBus`, no SSE endpoint, no `EventSource`, no token-in-URL). |
| Q7 | **Modal lifecycle**: focus-refetch + an `entitlements`-watching effect clears the "waiting for payment…" state on a balance increase; a 5-min frontend timeout re-enables buttons on abandonment. | Decouples the modal from Helio redirect fidelity; the server-side sweeper independently expires the orphan `pending` row at 30 min. |
| Q8 | **Hermetic acceptance** via `PAYMENTS_MOONPAY_API_STUB=1` (short-circuits `checkout_url` to a synthetic URL); the real Helio HTTP round-trip is covered by a per-release manual smoke. | `accept_payments.sh` can drive a stub flag from bash and stay fully offline; matches the "hermetic CI + manual smoke" philosophy. |
| Q9 | **Flat per-invocation fees** (A1) + **synchronous debit at command-issue time** (B2) + **API-layer guard pre-FSM** (C2). Spending integration = **M5**. | Engine FSMs stay payment-agnostic; M4 ships and is testable without spending wiring. (Unchanged from the original grill.) |

