## §3 Architecture surfaces

The structural point: **M4 adds no new HTTP routes and no new provider.** Checkout-start, the webhook, entitlements, and checkout-status endpoints all already exist and are provider-agnostic. M4 (a) un-gates a SKU, (b) makes `expired` a persisted state served by a sweeper, and (c) builds the frontend that drives and reflects the existing endpoints.

