- `db/queries/billing/row_mapping.rs` — `checkout_status_from_str`: keep the `"expired"` arm, **replace its stale comment** ("computed at read-time / data-integrity bug") with "persisted terminal state, written by the sweeper". No new arm needed (`failed` is out per Q5).
- `sweeper.rs` (new) — `pub async fn run_expiry_sweeper(pool: PgPool, interval: Duration) -> !`: `tokio::time::interval`, on each tick calls `checkouts::sweep_expired(&pool, Utc::now())` and logs the count. 30 s interval (matches the Iteration-4.A live-grace ticker).
- `lib.rs` — export `run_expiry_sweeper`. No router change.
- **No** `billing_cost_catalog.rs`, **no** `checkout_start_stripe.rs`, **no** `sse.rs`, **no** `StripeConfig`, **no** `secrets.rs` change — all were Stripe-lane artifacts.

**`atelier-backend/atelier-overseer/`** (gated) — boot path only.

- `src/main.rs` — after `AppState` construction (near the existing payments-router mount at ~:257), `tokio::spawn(atelier_payments::run_expiry_sweeper(pool.clone(), Duration::from_secs(30)));`.
