## §5 Acceptance gates — `accept_payments.sh`

Hermetic, ~10 s. Needs `docker compose -f docker-compose.beta.yml up -d`. Env: `MOONPAY_WEBHOOK_TOKEN_PAYLINK=test-paylink-token PAYMENTS_MOONPAY_API_STUB=1 AUTH_DEV_BYPASS=true` (+ dummy `MOONPAY_API_KEY_*` so the provider constructs).

| Gate | Check |
|------|-------|
| (i) Checkout start | `POST /api/payments/checkout/start {sku:"compute_credits",payment_method:"card_via_stripe"}` + `Authorization: Bearer dev-token` → `200` + `{checkout_id, url:"https://moonpay.stub/charge/…"}`. `psql`: `billing_checkouts` row `status='pending'`, `sku='atelier-credits-compute'`, `external_ref IS NULL`. |
| (ii) Webhook happy path | Forge a Helio `CREATED` payload with `additionalJSON.checkout_id=<checkout_id>` and `quantity:N`. POST `/payments/moonpay/webhook/paylink` with `Authorization: Bearer test-paylink-token` → `200`. `psql`: `billing_webhook_events` row inserted; `billing_checkouts.status='succeeded'`, `succeeded_at IS NOT NULL`; `billing_credit_ledger` 1 row (`kind='compute'`, `delta=N`, `reason='purchase'`, linked `checkout_id`). `GET /api/payments/entitlements` → `credits.compute == N`. |
| (iii) Replay | Re-POST identical payload → `200`. No new `billing_webhook_events` row, no new ledger row, balance unchanged. |
| (iv) Bad auth | POST with a wrong Bearer token → `401`. `psql`: no DB writes. |
| (v) Expiry sweep | Insert (or age) a `pending` checkout with `expires_at` in the past; run the sweeper (or wait one 30 s tick) → `psql`: that row is `status='expired'`, `expired_at IS NOT NULL`; a *fresh* `pending` row within its window is untouched. |

Exit 0 on all-pass; non-zero + descriptive log otherwise. Matches `accept_i4_5.sh`/`accept_w4a.sh` shape (sequential gates, `psql -A -t -c` assertions, trap cleanup on EXIT).

